  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Providing support for marketing of cocoa in West Sulawesi</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Amanah Cooperative, situated in Wonomulyo, Polewali Mandar District, West Sulawesi, was established in 2006 by 27 people of whom mostly farmers as a pre-cooperative. On 12 February 2007, Amanah was officially registered as a multi-business secondary cooperative. The cooperative collects cocoa out of 7 regions around Polman district and the plan is to expand to 9 regions in 2015. The members of Amanah are 7 primary cooperatives, consisting of farmer groups. The number of farmer groups has grown from 11 in 2007 to 84 farmer groups in the beginning of 2015.  Initially, the goal of Amanah is to secure the collection of cocoa by the primary cooperatives and offering services to the farmers as saving &amp; credit, training and communal purchasing of goods. In this process the cooperative is supported by Veco International, who funds technical support of local NGO and founder of Amanah, Wasiat. In March 2014, the buyer Armajaro indicated no longer to buy the cocoa of the farmer groups. After negotiations with PT Mars Symbioscience Indonesia corporation and collection of internal cash a marketing department was established by Amanah and purchasing and marketing of the cocoa was carried out by the cooperative. In this new role, the cooperative is undergoing some challenges such as: 
&#x2022;	Local buyers as competitors;
&#x2022;	Not enough cash flow to buy all the cocoa of the farmers;
&#x2022;	Different quality provided by farmers of each limited piece of land;
&#x2022;	Financial bookkeeping of marketing department is not developed yet;
&#x2022;	Limited enthusiasm of skilled farmers to take up positions in board and/or supervisory board.

As the cooperative already receives support on the level of technical support on production side, Agriterra will focus more on the development of the organisation, a.o. with governance support and training, improving the financial system and financial management training.

1) Improvement of governance
* Change the shares of marketing department into loan construction
* Train farmer group heads about role and responsibilities in cooperative
* Adjust the bylaws/statutes to current situation

2) Improvement of financial management
* Update knowledge about financial management
* Draft opening balance sheet for collective marketing unit 
* Set up temporarily system in Excel to keep track of stock in warehouse and to be able to draft balance sheet and profit and loss statement
* Set up of budget
* Find financial system for saving &amp; loan department and collective marketing to increase the repayment rate of the lenders</narrative>
  </description>
